### 3. Migration Strategy (Tool Capabilities)
- Overall migration approach (big bang vs phased, etc.)
- Prioritization criteria for objects
- Wave/batch planning strategy
- How the tool will orchestrate migrations

### 4. Factory Architecture (Tool Components)
- Core components of the migration factory
- Tools and technologies needed
- Integration points with source and target systems
- Data flow and processing pipelines

### 5. Migration Process Workflows (Tool Capabilities)
For each phase, specify inputs, activities, and outputs:
- Discovery and assessment phase
- Conversion/transformation phase
- Testing and validation phase
- Deployment phase
- Rollback procedures

### 6. Technical Mapping and Transformation Rules
- How source objects map to target components
- Transformation logic required
- Handling of unsupported features
- Metadata preservation strategy

### 7. Automation and Tooling
- What the tool will automate
- Custom scripts and utilities needed
- CI/CD integration approach
- Monitoring and logging capabilities

